caption: Small but good food
Good atmosphere with outside dining and great staff!

I love their chicken pho soup. The portions are enough for dinner and to have leftovers for the next day.  The quality of the soup never disappoints. I always ask for jalapeños on the side and extra bean sprouts. I love this place!
Good pho and love the option to sit outside as well!
This place is awesome the food around here is so good
Great food and service. Prices are reasonable and portion are just the ideal size. Food that makes me happy!
My sister and I got the jackfruit spring roll and it was AMAZING. Neither of us are vegan but it was so good.
Great staff, very clean practicing social distancing I had a coffee drink that was amazing
It's a good little Vietnamese cafe.
Staff were excellent
The food was amazing and fast ! Only thing, was when i walked in, i had to ask how seating worked, instead of being greeted.
Loved this place! Most definitely would go back. We need one of these in the Kansas City Area.
Enjoyed the atmosphere and food.

I wish I could give zero stars. Ordered an iced tea, came out after what felt like 30 mins (??) later AND there was literally one sad cube of ice. The drink was room temperature and tasted so bad. I only took one sip as I walked out the door and then I turned right around and came back. I drink boba teas very often and know that this was unacceptably low quality. I kindly asked if they could remake me another drink because of the poor quality and they REFUSED!!! They said I’d have to purchase another drink. They were RUDE. Bad boba drinks, worse customer service. I was truly bamboozled. I will never return and I will tell all my friends to never go here.

The Iced Tea changed my life! It's the best tea experience ever. Yum sip wow!  Please make sure the broth is always served HOT at safe temperature for fresh vegetables to be added for safety please!  Awesome vegan pho. Not too salty. Great flavor. Good tofu.
Luv this little place!
10/10. The Banh Mi sandwich was great! My girlfriend loved the Pho (she’s viet). We will be back. Great service.

Delicious!! They have options for Vegans, but i had  their BBQ Beef and it was DELICIOUS! Tender and flavorful, not spicy or bland. Perfect!! Also the thai iced tea, and the Taro boba were both amazing!!
Healthy and delicious. So many vegan options. Love the fresh rolls and pho noodle bowls
Delicious Pho
This is my favorite restaurant!!!!! So fresh, so good, so healthy. Also, the service is excellent. Especially with Hannah!! I can’t recommend this place enough.

This is one of my absolute favorite places. The food hits the mark everytime!!! And the service is always so pleasant, especially the manager Hannah. Definitely a regular stop of mine and at the top of my recommendations

I’ve only been to Bamboozle a few times since I no longer live in Florida, but every time I visit it’s a must stop! The atmosphere is always happy and welcoming, and the food is immaculate. Definitely worth the stop, and I highly recommend the beef pho!

First time today and the food was amazing!!! I got the BBQ jackfruit Banh Mi sandwich which was so JUICY!!! You haven’t lived until you have this amazing sandwich! Also the Boozle coffee with honeycomb crunch was delightful. Check this place out!!! You won’t be sorry!
Horrible service.  They bump express call ins for walk ins as long as there pretty women. Seriously!!!!
My top site for quality Asian food. Came here on a Friday I think. The staff was very helpful and welcoming. It has a good atmosphere.
Beautiful restaurant, reasonable prices and wonderful staff.
Great spot for asian food. Do yourself a favor and give this place a try. The staff was very helpful and observant.
Excellent Pho and Bahn Mi at reasonable prices. Very flavorful and fresh!  Clean and spacious with nice outdoor seating area and great service as well!
Nice site for quality asian food. prices were appropriate.
asian food, so fresh. The bill was fair for the quality of food. I can see why they have a lot of good reviews.

Smallest bowl of pho ever and I got the large Only one protein and to add another they wanted 6$ or something like that I barely ate any of it I love pho and this was not good I am so hungry and disappointed That def wasn’t like any pho I have ever tasted yuck I hate giving bad reviews but that was super over priced for very little they give you  When you order the fresh rolls they only give you one not two I ordered the duck one and it was tough and way to crispy and all you could taste was the over sweat sauce they brushed on the “duck” I only at half of it and the wrap def was not fresh or they didn’t make it fresh and out it in the fridge because it was thicker then normal and not as soft as real fresh rolls  The coconut tea thing was very good but not worth $5 Maybe 3.50 But the tapioca beads were too big to fit through their straws they give you and got very soggy very fast  I’m sorry for the bad review but that wasn’t good Goto a real pho spot this one is NOT IT!  Ohh and they serve it in a cardboard bowl 🍲

Went there around 3:30pm on 7/6/20. Service was extremely slow despite us being the only ones in the entire place when we arrived nor did they seem to have a clue how to run a business efficiently. Not a single person greeted us like we were a burden on them. If you order from here, call ahead by 2 hours and your food might be ready by the time you arrive.
Thai tea and wraps are refreshing but the customer service and time management needs to be improved.

Since the refurb, the prices have gone up but the portions of meat has gone down significantly,  Basically now just a bowl of cheap noodles with tiny amounts of chicken or beef, but you then have to pay more  Disappointed

This place is truly authentic Neapolitan pizzeria with very friendly staff and adorable decor. They used fresh Italian ingredients like smoked  mozzarella (provola).  The place is small but the food is great. Their fresh dough combined with the real wood fired oven makes their pizzas so wonderful.  I will recommend the pizza called "crema di tartufo" it is very unique and delicious.  I will definitely come back to this place. Actually I have been here two times in a row. Great place to satisfy my pizza cravings.  By they way, I got a free Nutella crepe with my Yelp check-in. And the next day they let me switch it for a cannoli ricotta. Both were DELISH.
Best smoothie I've ever had
They have 1 speed SLOW! Waited over 30 mins to get 1 drink of boba
Nice selection of Asian inspired sandwiches spiked with cilantro..
The pho soup is great!  The Staff is friendly and the service is wonderful!  I love coming here for lunch!

Great little Vietnamese cafe in the heart of Channelside. The fresh rolls were packed with fresh veg and tasty proteins, in our case chicken and shrimp. The beef pho was warm and flavorful and the pork bahn mi was spicy.
Love this location!!!
Vegan Pho was delicious, exactly what I've been craving lately. Cute and comfy atmosphere, free wifi, staff was super friendly. Good place to study
Great boba tea, just took a little longer then expected.

There are two Bamboozle locations, one here in Channelside and one Downtown.  They both have different interiors which convey a different atmosphere.  Channelside location is laidback with wooden tables that remind me of restaurants in Asia.  The food is excellent in both locations.  I ordered the Banh Mi and the bread was fresh, warm and soft.  Whatever filling you get, you don’t be disappointed.  Give them a try!
good food
Quaint little place that was located conveniently close to our hotel. The food was delicious and was served fast and hot. Definitely a place I'd like to revisit.
Love this place! Fast service and great people. Plenty of options for Vegans and Vegetarians. Personal favs- Banh Mi-Vegan, Vegan Pho and Avocado-Mango Rolls.
You will not be disappointed!They were amazing. Honestly the best tasting sandwiches I've had.
Rolls are very good.
Awesome place!  Good food, reasonable prices.  Cozy, friendly, super casual and simple.
Friendly staff, a limited yet varied menu. Prices are fair. The limeade was delicious. Didn't see a bathroom anywhere and the space was small.
Service is super slow. Waiters doesn’t even clean up the mess on other tables. We waited for more than 20 minutes for our starters.
Delicious vegan pho.
Small and cozy, but food was not good. The pho broth felt bland and diluted and only 4-5 thin slices of beef in the big size choice. It was 10$ but it was a perfectly wasted 10$.
Had the Shrimp Pho and it was really good! First time here from MN. Cute restaurant, friendly workers.

Expect to wait more than 20 minutes on food and drink regardless of placing an online order ahead of time, they still take forever to make your food! They have the best Taro Boba Milk Tea in town, just not sure why everytime I go here the orders take more than 20 minutes despite 3-4 people working at one time.

Our daughter who is vegetarian brought us to this cafe type downtown restaurant. We all ordered a variety of the rolls (small) including chicken, tofu lemongrass and avocado. We each had two rolls. I personally could have used a third. One orders at the counter and then they bring the rolls to your table. The ingredients were fresh and the rolls made as they are ordered. We enjoyed our meals. We just had water so we can't comment on the milk drinks or smoothies. They say that they are gluten free and do not use MSG. The no MSG is important to us since my wife adversely reacts to it. It was dog friendly with several dogs in the outside area. It was a pleasant place to have lunch.

When entering you still feel like your entering someone's house with relaxed people, some just reading. The patron popped out from the back with a big smile and asked how I was.  The genuine positivity was as great start to my day as I could ask for.  We chatted a bit (it wasn't a busy morning for either of us), and decided on the iced cappuccino and a thick slice of the tortilla pie.
Staff can be a little short with you but the products are fantastic!
Best blueberry smoothies ever! Love the haas avocado wrap! Never dissapointed with their food! Sometimes theres a bit of a wait but the food makes it worth it!
Very kind service. Front end kids were great. Unfortunately the chicken was so dry that there was not enough sauce to make up for it.

When you Bamboozle Channelside "best seafood restaurant" in Tampa, FL," Bamboozle Channelside is the very first to pop up.  The reviews really speak for themselves.  The delicious food quality, affordable prices, impeccable service, and intimate modern ambiance makes this family-owned restaurant a favorite for locals and out of towners.

Shrimp spring rolls where frozen, and so were cucumber and lettuce pieces.  The best fresh rolls have the shrimp still warm as it’s been cooked fresh and not frozen or pre made and kept too cold, plus the flavor was just poor.  The pho was equally disappointing - I got the shrimp and the shrimp were Tiger Prawns, so great quality shrimp but just not prepared correctly, they were very fleshy and undercooked as if they had just dropped them in the hot water and hoped they would cook by the time they got to me - at least that’s how they tasted in the event they were also previously frozen and dropped in.  I know good Vietnamese and sadly this wasn’t it here today for me.

Wow! Every woman in this restaurant was super friendly. The food bright, fresh and delicious and reasonably priced. They have a buffet of vegs, meats, herbs and sauces. So you can create your own dish. And... I love that you can have a short bowl of Pho and Ban Mi or roll. Superb!
Delicious ,fresh and so healthy!

Happened upon this tea room/cafe while at Channelside, and will be returning soon. We had the Tiger rolls, pho, and the pork banh mi. All were excellent, even the fresh coconut water was great. They advertise as Asian flare in a French atmosphere, and they didn't disappoint. Also helps that a dog run is just across the street, so sitting at the high counter and looking out the window was fun.
Long wait
Hands down THE BEST pho I’ve ever had. Really charming little place, great service, and a patio that allows doggies :)
One of my fav locations for tasty Vietnamese food. Food was so appetizing. The staff was very welcoming and sociable. Feels like a place in Los Angeles I liked.

vietnamese food... very delicious. Nice place to relax, people watch, eat good, etc.  I've had nothing but great experiences here and will keep coming back. Prices that are reasonable. Feels similar to a cafe in Chicago I loved.
Extremely poor service and no willingness to correct or make it right. I am (was) a repeat customer. No more.
I love the buba over here
Had the BBQ pork bahn mi. Highly recommend

What’s up with the good reviews!? Ok I’m from LA where we have great pho. This was by far the worst pho I’ve ever had! Just beef or chicken rlly? Where’s the tripe? The tendons? Meatballs? Oh and forgetting all that the portion of beef was super skimpy. Don’t go here!
Had the chicken roll and chicken sandwich.... absolutely awesome! I suggest having both aioli sauces on the sandwich!
Very good pho!!!
Pretty awful boba, won't be returning.

I was pretty disappointed in this place. I had a boba tea and it wasn't that good. I also tried the coffee which was okay. The menu wasn't too much to brag about. it was not busy at all. It was easy to spot from the road. They did have a food menu but I did not try it.

A fantastic Asian-Fusion cafe.  Had the Traditional Banh Mi, and the Taro Milk drink.  The Banh Mi wasn't technically using a chicken pate, but it still tasted delicious, as did the Taro Milk Drink.  The interior was very well optimized, and had a lot of character to it.  Staff was very good as well, very friendly and attentive
Difficult to find somewhere to park and the food was just ok.  French's Fried onions on the pho was a fail
Love it.  Best pho I've ever had!
Best vegan bahn mi I've ever eaten.  The tofu flavor and texture was perfect.  All the ingredients were fresh, all the expected accoutrements were available.
(Translated by Google) Welcoming staff and fair price  (Original) Personnel accueillant et prix correct
Food was fresh and well cooked very friendly environment and they also have an outdoor setting. Very refreshing.
The food and service is great.
Food was fantastic and Michael our server put it over the top.

caption: Decent food. Good service but im love w/ food in california and texas  great Vietnamese food , we get in close , ist good for tampa
Great food! A little pricey, and it should open at 11 instead of 11:30. The tables inside are painted and that gives them a sticky texture - a minor quibble

My pho was pretty good.  I finished it.  A touch too sweet and did not have much of the fresh sprouts and greens taste some pho has.  Like the downtown branch it was not quite as comfortable as I would have liked, ambiance-wise. It was ok though.
Food was extremely flavorful and fresh. Good vegan options. Friendly service. Great location. Just can’t beat that!
Coozy place 👌
Nice clean Gluten-free organic and well that’s good stuff

I'm a fan of this place, especially if you're in the area/ around channelside. The last several times I've visited have been at nighttime which have all be pleasant experiences. However, I recently visited in the daytime and it was quite lovely. They allow outdoor full service seating if you bring your puppy. Directly across the street is a small park to walk your dog too. So while I have enjoyed this venue at night, my daytime visit has been that much more enjoyable. The atmosphere is decent. Not mind blowing or overly nice, pretty simple in nature (ie the floors are concrete,the tables are not matching, and the ambiance is a little confusing). But all things considered, it's a solid "4-star" boba cafe.  I appreciate their vegan/vegetarian options and the array they serve of foods and teas. There is a little something here for everyone. The staff has always been helpful and nice.~ even if it doesn't become your #1 spot, it's worth a visit.

The banh mi at this place was killer and authentic. The pho was also tasty in its own right with a lean, but powerful, broth that had a hint of coconut. Overall, great location with a dog friendly patio and tasty food.
Awesome place with good, tasty Vietnamese food! Yum! 😋 🍜
Always will be my favorite pho place in Tampa. The kickin chicken roll is great too
The Pho was fantastic! I also enjoyed their Sake. Overall, it was a good first experience here. I’ll be back!

Their food is always amazing, but they don’t have their stuff together. I ordered a simple takeout - two fresh rolls. Small, quick order. She said it would take 10 minutes and it took 35 minutes!! The restaurant wasn’t even busy, so I’m not sure what took so long. I was honestly raging by the time I got the food and didn’t even enjoy it.

Food was ok. We ordered a banh mi, pho, noodle salad, and spring rolls. A lot of the food left us wishing there was more flavor to it. The best thing we got were the spring rolls, which were a bit overpriced.

It was my first time in Tampa and I wanted to check if there were any similarities between the Bay Area and Tampa. Tried the Taiwan. Very interesting and the first time anyone's ever told me to smell the ingredients to get a feel for the taste. I give it a 3/5 because the drink was what I expected. The boba/tapioca was very poor quality, you can chew it and know it was frozen. I also asked for less ice and I got a whole scoop of ice, making up 1/3 of my drink full of ice. Also they don't use real tea, it's all powder.

The food is GREAT! BUT, They can not get an order correct. Something is always wrong or missing. Today my daughter came in with a $35.00 order. Isaid did you check it? She said NO! I said I will bet you that meal cost it is wrong. I won! She asked for four GINGER SAUCES WE GOT FOUR PEANUT. They are six for six with me. Thank the lord it is all good!

Awesome staff and great food. Smoothies are delicious too.  I have uncommon food allergies, and it makes eating out difficult. When I spoke to staff about them, they went above and beyond. Asked about all of my allergies, how severe they are, explained which sauces are safe for me, et cetera. Best restaurant experience I've ever had with staff.
Nice location, Excellent food...
Good food, good people, good vibes. . . . !
my wife and I stopped in on our way to Bradenton fl and loved it greatly.

Not sure why there are so many 5 star reviews. Came in with a party of 4. (No other customers  besides us) Ordered our food and drinks. (BBQ pork bahn mi, grilled chicken bahn mi, iced Vietnamese coffee, ice Thai Tea with boba, Taiwan Black Tea with boba, mango dragon fruit with jelly) 10 minutes pass and server walks up to us to tell us they don't have any more Thai Tea. We request for iced matcha tea latte.  10 more minutes pass (other customers arrive. Party of 5) and server brings us 2/4 drinks (Taiwan Black Tea and Iced Matcha tea latte). 1/5 stars for both of the drinks. The Taiwan Black Tea tasted watered down and the Iced Matcha tea latte tasted like fish sauce. I asked my girlfriend if she wanted a different drink but she insisted she didn't want to wait another 20 minutes for a drink.  5 minutes later our food came out with our 3rd drink. ( 25 minutes and 3/4 drinks have arrived.) Upon looking at our food, it was visually appealing. That was about the only thing appealing about the two bahn mi. The meat was precooked and cool to the touch. Grilled chicken looked/tasted as if it was precooked and frozen. And the grilled pork tasted like beef jerky. The only saving thing for the bahn mi was that the bread was toasted and tasted good.  15 minutes later (so 40 minutes all together) my iced Vietnamese coffee arrives after finishing our food. The coffee was okay. Not good. Not bad.  Servers were very monotone and unenthusiastic.  Will not be returning to this restaurant. You can say that we were "bamboozled".

Love Bamboozle Channelside and their amazing customer service!!! I called very soon before closing time and they were happy to take my order (even though they had broke down the kitchen). The staff was friendly. And I totally appreciate the accommodation! Thank you!!!

I don't understand the high ratings here.  We each had a bowl of pho and spring rolls.  The spring rolls were good but not as good as the other places downtown.  The pho was not good at all.  The wife had shrimp which was very overcooked and rubbery.  The beef in mine was also very dry and overcooked.  I cannot be sure because I was not in the kitchen but it seems as if they cook the meat before they let the pho cook it.  The broth was also made with waaaaay too much cilantro (or other green leafy herb).  Every bite would have a leaf.  I am only giving a second star because of the atmosphere and their friendly attitude to dogs.  There are many good Vietnamese options in downtown Tampa, I would reccomend going to one of them instead of this place.
If this place wasn't in the heart of downtown and impossible to find parking I would eat there everyday. It's So Delicious from the fresh spring rolls to the curry this is a definite home run.

Amazing teas and food. We have done some events for our company here and its always such a pleasant experience. The owner Lynn and her staff always go above and beyond to make our visit to Bamboozle Tea Lounge unforgettable. If you have never been to this place, we recommend to come by and try their Citron Green iced tea and their Banh Mi sandwich. You wont be disappointed!

The food is ok, decent price, slow service, and inconsistent product. I suggest retraining staff to improve ticket times. I have been coming here for 3 years and the first year I loved it and slowly the employees and their attention to detail have changed and it's clear they don't always properly follow the recipe.  My biggest complaint is with the drinks. Employees don't follow the same recipe making the boba smooties. Sometimes the drinks are perfect and other times they are too sweet. So I asked then to make it less sweet and then it wasn't sweet at all. The boba is often under boiled and hard in the middle, however the last time it was way too soft and dissolved in the drink and was barely chewy.  It has been a month since my last visit. I do plan to come back but haven't had a good experience my last 5 visits. I hope this business will become more consistent because I do love their concept.

They have amazing PHO!!! I love the welcoming environment and home feeling you get right when you walk in. very fast and very nice staff, great place to hang out with some friends and eat some great food! My friends and I try to come here as often as we can, I love the Vegan Pho that they have it taste so good!!!
This place is amazing!   Great food and wonderful service.
The Mango-Jackfruit Smoothie with boba was delicious, and not too sweet. The service was very good and friendly.
Great bubble tea. Not many places in Tampa where you can get a milk tea most the locations in south and west Tampa closed down. Their food is light but filling.
Great pho and spring rolls in a quaint spot. They also advertise as a tea room, but it's not a hoity-toity place.
Love the Vietnamese food options.
Great Pho and Bahn Mhi! The staff is small but nice and polite!
The food, the setting, the people, the Vietnamese coffee are all so sweet!

In Tampa for conference went here for 3 days in a row for lunch.  Nice options sandwiches, salads, rolls, and pho.  Good options for vegetarians and lactose intolerant.  Depending on time of day that you come service can be slow if we were there mid lunch time the first time service okay the next day we were the first ones there and service great. Dogs allowed outside full-service outside.  Nice interior setup, same-sex bathroom.  Smitty's also available as well as beer and wine.
Very good phô... I fell in love with their milk drinks, especially the Lavender and the Taro flavors.
The food is always great, and the blueberry banana smoothie I got was sweet, delicious and fresh!
Fantastic! So glad they put a new location in Channelside.
Incredible gem in Chanelside, Tampa! Boba tea is incredible and their pork BBQ is bomb! Great live entertainment.
Great place great food.
Chicken pho is so yummy and their sandwich bread mmmmm.

The customer service was very rude and I received a poor welcoming attitude from the cashier . They made me feel like I was unwelcome with me and my friend . For my first time experience there, I wish it was more pleasant. However, I did enjoy the boba and the relaxing atmosphere .
Rice Noodle bowl for the win!!(BBQ Pork)
Wonderful employees!  The food and service together makes this place my favorite! Very calming atmosphere that is ideal for catching up on work or chatting with a friend.
I had the pork Bahn Mi, which was pretty good. Bubble tea was decent, as well.
Such a nice place to go, the owner and her assistant are wonderful and we enjoyed Our Tea immensely.
Love this place, I come here almost every week. The food is amazing, I come for the rolls but also love the smoothies and the phos. The place is nice and the staff is friendly. I highly recommend!
Delicious shrimp spring roll and shrimp pho
Love their fresh spring rolls
Fantastic drinks and food. Not a bad item on the menu and fair priced.
It's good
Food is very good, prices are high for Viet food.  Building and location are great but it took quite a while to get our food and many orders were incorrect.
My favorite place for Pho when I'm in Tampa !

A group of four of us stopped in before a mid-afternoon trip to the aquarium. We had high expectations and found ourselves a little disappointed. All of our food and drinks were okay but each item left us thinking it could've/should've been just a bit better. The chicken bahn mi and strawberry pineapple smoothie got highest marks — probably 4 stars. The strawberry smoothie and taro bubble tea were just okay. The BBQ pork was very good but the spring roll was larger than I'm used to, wasn't well wrapped, and the lettuce had a number of brown pieces. The beef and pork on the noodle salads were similarly very good, as was the fresh mango, but the proportions seemed off and the pickled ginger wasn't a great surprise. The peanut sauce also seemed a little off. Service was okay — not overly friendly or motivated but okay. Everything came out at different times, so our meal together was a little awkward. But it's a nice and interesting atmosphere (dog friendly!) and we'd probably try it again.
Food is fresh and tasty.

After taking my toddler to the aquarium we were looking for food options nearby. I couldn’t be happier that Bamboozle Tea Lounge showed up.  The chicken pho had such depth of flavor, we’re still talking about it. We also had the beef and avocado rolls which were perfect for a light lunch.  Extremely baby/toddler friendly. Lovely staff.

This used to be a gem but quality has unfortunately gone downhill, my last three sittings left to desire. Pho soup has repeatedly been bland w very little chicken or shrimp portions.  The presentation of the side veggies for soup seemed careless.  Regardless I might have been unlucky but feel I wont give another shot here. Location and decoration are super cool.
Great customer service, great food, great vibes. 10/10
Knowledgeable & friendly staff, great food!

Good food but service needs improvement. We have been going to both the tea lounge and the cafe for some time and it seems service needs to be improved at both places. The tea lounge stuff specifically seems like is not paying much attention to your needs, you need to ask for everything and they almost seem apathetic to customers.

Great find! The fruit smoothies are full of flavor and you can really taste the fruit. The food is very delicious although a bit dry so use the sauces at the table and the pho tasted pretty authentic. However it is a little more expensive than other places but definitely worth it!

Amazing veggie Pho. A top 3 contender in all of Florida.  The soup alone is worth the trip. Order the tofu rice rolls with it. Wash it down with a cool fruit smoothie or take home a bottle of wine. You won't be disappointed.

Just got milk tea. The boba was still hard and the tea was small for the price, $5.35. The women serving us wasn't very kind. I'm hoping she just had a bad day. The environment was very cute and the pho smelled good!
Delicious pho and rolls, quick and friendly
Had bahn mi and spring rolls during a dine-in visit to one of the best restaurants I've ever patronized!
Very health quiet and local spot. Everyone loves this place.
Kickin chicken is sooooo good!
Yummy deliciousness
Great pho, great smoothies with boba, great people and service!
They aight. The customer service was not the best but the food was AMAZING!
Have always loved Bamboozle. The pho is delicious as are the many different kinds of spring rolls. Healthy and Gluten friendly, can't beat it!!
Excellent food and a wonderfully friendly staff.

Absolutely amazing food and tea! Had the small vegan Pho that had super flavorful broth and the BBQ pork bahnmi, my dad got the small chicken Pho with a two different spring rolls! Perfect amount of food. Go eat here please

Not authentic Vietnamese food, more like a sad attempt at it while trying to be cool to hipsters. Everything tastes bland and not seasoned, and dry. Not to mention we placed our order, waited for over 20 minutes standing around and waiting, only for the staff to not acknowledge what was going on with our food. We ask them what’s taking so long, only to find out they never made it. Great job Bamboozle, you bamboozled us into paying for over priced tasteless Vietnamese food.
This place is quaint and nice. Came on a Friday when people were singing karaoke. It was a little loud but great place to be. There fresh vegan rolls are amazing as well as their vegan pho!
Love the food and the atmosphere. Customers and staff were awesome.
Fantastic!!
Outstanding!
Pretty authentic Vietnamese food. The seating area is pretty basic, and small.

We come here Almost weekly since we live near by. Love, love the rolls and the boba tea smoothies. Only complaint is the service is hit or miss... sometimes our order comes out perfectly but I would say 50% of the time they mess it up. It depends who's working that day but we sometimes become hesitant as to whether or not get dinner there as we risk our order being wrong :/

Great food, gluten free options for people that are gluten sensitive. NOT celiac friendly, had a noodle plate there and now having a major reaction. If you are vegetarian, gluten sensitive, or have no allergies then it is a great place to go.
Great soups and spring rolls, beer and wine available.
Great food, good prices. Only issue is minimal to no parking spots available around the cafe.
Delicious mango boba smoothie
Health food.
Oh so good. There are no adequate words
Quaint little place with its own unique personality. We stopped in had the mini pho and was not disappointed.

The staff here is top notch and it's clear they take pride in the quality of work they do. Not to mention the food is great (the chicken banh mi is my favorite). Really just an excellent spot in a great urban space with lots of cool events throughout the week to bring people in.
Great menu, very flavorful food, lots of vegan & vegetarian options, nice atmosphere, friendly staff
Great lunch in a cozy atmosphere. Rolls or soup you can't go wrong. Parking lot is around the corner on Channelside.
Food is awesome!!  Cool chill atmosphere and super friendly staff.  Fresh and quick..a great option on the go!  Try the boba tea and BBQ pork bahn mi they won't let you down.
Perfection!
Place is the best!! Except when Alexis jokes that they're out of whatever I want that day and I fall for it. Then they're just really good.
Great food!!!

My mom and I visited for the first time for the Mother's Day brunch that we had heard from the owners at the downtown location was going on.  However, the staff at this location knew nothing of the event, did not know how to sell us the bulk tea that was listed, and were overall a bit confounded at many of our requests that were listed on their menus.  However, the staff were all easy-going laughing and were excellent through out the visit doing their best to help.  The food was excellent and the atmosphere cozy.  I would definitely recommend the tea lounge on Channelside but maybe call ahead if your interested in bulk tea purchases!
Super chill, non-pretentious tea lounge. Welcoming and FRESH! Food and tea is great! Bonus: you can order ahead online!!! Love it!
Love this spot! Always laid back, great spring rolls!
Great place for noodles, very reasonably priced.
Authentic food
Great food. Affordable prices. Cute design.
Smoothie was made with fresh strawberries!

Great bah mi, pho, and fresh salads. A word of warning when ordering online during lunch hours: the 20 wait is a bit optimistic. It's usually 40-50 minutes before your food will be ready. It's still worth the wait though!

I knew as soon as I called Lynn at Bamboozle Tea Lounge to set up our Baby Shower, things were going to be great! This charming tea eatery in the Channelside locale is hard to beat. There were numerous tea flavors hot or iced. Several specialty drink choices added flare, as well . And the wonderfully fresh and edgy Asian fare was appealing to all. There were even yummy dessert options . Beautiful presentation and delicious  choices for everyone's tastes.  The atmosphere was charming and relaxing and just perfect for a get together or a luncheon party. The efficient service, helpfulness and etiquette of the manager and staff were beyond expectations. My guests and "mommy to be" (who became a mommy now) were thrilled with our day at Bamboozle and would highly recommend this charming cafe. Thank you so much again to all at Bamboozle Tea Lounge !
The food here is amazing and it makes up for the lack of service the employees give. It takes them a while to prepare the food so give yourself ample time or call ahead and take out.
Real nice people and great services we enjoy our food and good experience with delicious tea

My mom recently held my baby shower here and it was just perfect! Very nice staff and helpful great food and tea:) couldn't have asked for a better shower. Definitely recommend very pleasant and inviting!

The service was excellent, they guided us through the menu since it was are first time and were extremely friendly. The pho was some of the best I have had. Their summer roll selection is extensive and they are really good. We tried the traditional roll and my favorite part was the peanut sauce, most places it is usually too sweet but theirs is perfect. Finally their milk teas are perfect I got the matcha and my fiance got the almond. Great experience, would definitely return regularly if I didn't live in Orlando!

I hosted my best friends bridal shower here this past Sunday. Let me tell you, this is the place to have a small get together! The food was super fresh and delicious! The Tea and Sangria were very refreshing. From coordinating with Lynn for this special day to arriving and having the help of Robin, Noel and Tommie was great! Tommie was a HUGE help with hanging my decorations and taking them down for me. Thank you ALL so very much!
Good Pho and fresh rolls. Busy at lunch M-F.

Again, everything about Bamboozle is great; the price and portions of the food to the cozy atmosphere.  I had the kickin chicken vermicelli noodles, and although $8.50 was a dollar more than I would have liked (only item I'll criticize), it was  tasty.  The pho comes in a great portion at a great price, and the place in general puts a creative twist on Vietnamese food.
Great pho!
Sooo yummy! Great smoothies and food!
Tasty at a sensibke no rip off price.  Healthy food.
Very hipsterish without the hipsters! Great Pho for the affordable price.
I got the kicking chicken rolls and a honeydew Smoothie, both were delicious, quickly served and reasonably priced. I will be coming back next time I visit Tampa, highly recommended.

The food is good but today the service was terrible. It took an extra 30min after I got there for an online order that was placed 30minutes prior to my and my co workers arrival. It also had ingredients on it that I requested not be on it so I ended up not eating it. Better inventory management is nice as well because things seem to always be out when we are there. We enjoy coming here for lunch on the weekend but this makes us hesitant about coming back.  Outside of that we usually enjoy coming here.
Cute, little tea shop. Whether you're vegetarian, vegan, or a meat eater, there is food for you.
Everything about this place is great! Awesome staff, delicious food, and nice prices!
Boba tea is delicious!
Outstanding.  Very friendly and quaint with extremely fresh food.
Nice little tea house. Great teas and good food.
Cold noodle salad.... WINNER!

My friend Patsy likes to come here and so I go along. I have to get used to smaller lighter portions of food I guess. This type of food is all new to me but I am willing to open myself up to a new experience like this.  I do like the Baby Noodle Salads and the teas are interesting. As long as Patsy likes to come here I will be with her. ;-)  p.s. I wish they had free refills on the tea!
I am vegan and was very impressed by my avacado roll and tofu sandwich. The presentation was exceptional and the meal was so delicious. Yum!
It is amazing! Any person reading this must go here! The prices are great and the food is yum! Order the beef Pho and bottomless tea.
All around great. This is a MUST try and I guarantee you will be back.
Perfection. Excellent service with excellent food with an excellent atmosphere. Give Tai a raise, the boy is a legend.
Excellent food and service. Avoid going during peak lunch hours as the wait can get rather long.
Always fresh!!!
Great food all around. Can't go wrong with the pho. Prices are good here too.
This is a nice little place! The drinks and food are refreshing and the prices are reasonable for a healthy snack. I would recommend it!
